            <title>[SUREFIRE-538] Surefire-booter and surefire-integration-tests require 1.4 but fail to specify it in their POMs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-538</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Surefire-booter and surefire-integration-tests require 1.4 but fail to specify it in their POMs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Class SurefireBooter uses the constructor RuntimeException(String, Exception) which was introduced in Java 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Likewise HelperAssertions.extractReports().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either the code needs to be changed, or the pom needs to specify Java 1.4 as a minimum.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
